== 冲击 ==
纪录片对索科国际提起的指控，得到当地的致力于国家公园的非政府组织和民间社会组织的支持，他们把压力加大，迫使公司结束石油勘探工作<ref>{{cite web|title=WWF calls on Soco to explain Virunga allegations in new film|url=http://www.wwf.org.uk/wwf_articles.cfm?unewsid=7131|website=WWF.org|publisher=WWF|accessdate=20 August 2014|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304192011/http://www.wwf.org.uk/wwf_articles.cfm?unewsid=7131|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2014年6月11日，索科国际和[[世界自然基金会|世界自然基金会]]公布了一份联合声明，石油公司承诺“在未获得教科文组织和刚果政府的同意下，不进行或委托任何在维龙加国家公园进行勘探和钻探的工作，这些活动不符合世界遗产的地位<ref>{{cite web|title=SOCO and WWF agree way forward on future activity in Virunga National Park (DRC)|url=http://www.socointernational.com/soco-and-wwf-agree-way-forward-on-future-activity-|website=Soco International|accessdate=20 August 2014|archive-date=2018-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704010001/https://www.socointernational.com/soco-and-wwf-agree-way-forward-on-future-activity-|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”该举动被广泛认为是世界自然基金会在这场赶走索科的战役中的胜利，制片人也获得了信誉。然而，该协议的公信力得到制片人<ref>{{cite web|title=Soco International’s Latest Move in Virunga National Park Leaves More Questions than it Answers|url=http://virungamovie.com/blog/details/8001/soco-internationals-latest-move-in-virunga-national-park-leaves-more-questions-than-it-answers|website=Virunga (Official Website)|accessdate=20 August 2014|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202055910/https://virungamovie.com/blog/details/8001/soco-internationals-latest-move-in-virunga-national-park-leaves-more-questions-than-it-answers|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[全球见证|全球见证]]<ref>{{cite web|title=British oil company’s back-tracking on World Heritage Site looks like a ruse|url=http://www.globalwitness.org/library/british-oil-company%E2%80%99s-back-tracking-world-heritage-site-looks-ruse|website=Global Witness|accessdate=20 August 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001074144/http://www.globalwitness.org/library/british-oil-company%E2%80%99s-back-tracking-world-heritage-site-looks-ruse|archivedate=2014年10月1日}}</ref>和[[人权观察|人权观察]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sawyer|first1=Ida|title=Dispatches: Congo’s Virunga Park Rangers, Activists Still Need Justice|url=http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/06/11/dispatches-congo-s-virunga-park-rangers-activists-still-need-justice|accessdate=20 August 2014|work=Human Rights Watch|publisher=Human Rights Watch|date=11 June 2014|archive-date=2015-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150729165823/http://www.hrw.org/news/2014/06/11/dispatches-congo-s-virunga-park-rangers-activists-still-need-justice|dead-url=no}}</ref>等其他非政府组织和当地民间社会组织<ref>{{cite web|title=Congo Civil Society Express Concerns About SOCO’s Deal With WWF on Virunga Oil Exploration|url=http://www.africanconservation.org/in-focus/virunga/item/congo-civil-society-express-concerns-about-soco-s-deal-with-wwf-on-virunga-oil-exploration|website=African Conservation Foundation|publisher=African Conservation Foundation|accessdate=20 August 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006202228/http://www.africanconservation.org/in-focus/virunga/item/congo-civil-society-express-concerns-about-soco-s-deal-with-wwf-on-virunga-oil-exploration|archivedate=2014年10月6日}}</ref>的强烈关注。

世界自然基金会的高管承认，维龙加的战斗很难结束。索科尚未放弃经营许可或承诺无条件撤离，按照该组织的全球运动总监扎克·亚伯拉罕的说法，“他们还在打开大门<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/16/world/oil-dispute-takes-a-page-from-congos-bloody-past.html?_r=0|title=Oil Dispute Takes a Page From Congo’s Bloody Past|date=2014-11-15|accessdate=2014-11-18|archive-date=2018-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118172751/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/16/world/oil-dispute-takes-a-page-from-congos-bloody-past.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

